"Obama has proposed 442 tax hikes since taking office," said Americans for Tax Reform in an April 14 press release .
Americans for Tax Reform is well known for opposing tax increases.
(Indeed, we track 24 campaign promises from Obama on the topic of taxes, a group that includes proposed tax hikes as well as proposed tax breaks.)
Americans for Tax Reform agreed that four of the items we found were not tax increases, including the repeal of the telephone excise tax.
Our rulingAmericans for Tax Reform said that "Obama has proposed 442 tax hikes since taking office."